Sadiq Umar joining Villarreal is off the table after Arnaut Danjuma could not agree personal terms with Premier League club, West Ham. According to transfer expert Fabrizio Romano, Villarreal was  keen to sign Sadiq should Danjuma move back to the Premier League with West Ham. “West Ham wanted him (Danjuma) and were in advanced talks with Villarreal days ago, then negotiations off because of personal terms,” reported Romano on Twitter. “No agreement, still the same situation. “Villarreal wants Sadiq but Danjuma is not close to leaving now.” Super Eagles striker, Sadiq Umar has been linked with several top clubs across Europe after his goals helped UD Almeria to return to La Liga for the new season.